profile:
Certified Interior Decorator, Hunter Douglas – Certified Professional & Member of the Canadian Decorators’ Association
Teresa Alice is also an amateur photographer, Mosaicist & DIY’er (since the age of gluing macaroni to a paper plate). Although she has spent most of her working years in hospitality & insurance fields, this has enabled Teresa Alice to perfect her compassion for clients’ needs and successful project management skills. While decorating has always been a passion, it was decided to pursue it full-time and attended Durham College to complete her Interior Decorator’s Certification. With Presidential Honours received Teresa Alice went on to create a cutting-edge client satisfaction driven decorating service, Conundrum Decor.

Teresa Alice’s creative thinking pertaining to harmony within your living/work space has furthered her addiction for colour and furnishings.  Her ability to add spice to a space is uniquely provided through her upholstery, window coverings and paint work. Just need help pulling your decor project together? Teresa Alice will help with choosing a colour palette with coordinating fabrics, throw pillows, rugs and any other decor pieces required for your project.

Teresa Alice’s source of creativity is her side-kick Dover! Dover faithfully keeps her company through her hours of painting and designing. He is always looking for new friends and loves to travel.
